<h2 class="n">Our Faculty</h2><p>The School of Music contracts experienced faculty holding music degrees and/or proficiency as professionals in their instrument. Complete background checks are performed on all instructors. Our professional instructors are active in local bands, choirs, orchestras, music associations, and musical groups.</p><h3>Meet Our Instructors</h3><h4><img src="http://www.pcctoday.com/monkimage.php?mediaDirectory=mediafiles&amp;mediaId=390272&amp;fileName=graphic--staff-photo--laird-halling--001--jpg-0-0-107-150.jpg" width="107" height="150" alt="GRAPHIC : STAFF PHOTO : Laird Halling : 001 : JPG" title="GRAPHIC : STAFF PHOTO : Laird Halling : 001 : JPG" style="float: left; padding-right: 25px; padding-bottom: 25px;">Laird Halling,&nbsp;School Director [ saxophone, clarinet, flute ]</h4><p>Laird has been a professional musician and instructor for over 30 years, performing in a variety of jazz and classical groups. He has a Bachelor of Music degree in Composition from Marylhurst University, is a published arranger, and has worked for 25 years writing music for and directing music groups in churches. He recently toured with jazz bands to Scotland and Finland.&nbsp;</p><p><a href="http://youtu.be/l8JuLMuM2_Q" class="button"><span>Click here to listen to My Concert in Scotland!</span></a></p><div class="clr">&nbsp;</div><h4><img src="http://www.pcctoday.com/monkimage.php?mediaDirectory=mediafiles&amp;mediaId=1682653&amp;fileName=graphic--school-of-music--christina-marino-0-0-107-135.jpg" width="107" height="135" alt="GRAPHIC : School of Music : Christina Marino" title="GRAPHIC : School of Music : Christina Marino" style="float: left; padding-right: 25px; padding-bottom: 25px;">Cristina Marino [ voice, piano, violin ]</h4><p>Cristina has a Bachelor of Arts degree from Lewis &amp; Clark College, a Bachelor of Music degree in voice from Portland State University, and a Masters of Music degree in voice from the San Francisco Conservatory of Music. She sings in the Portland Opera Chorus, has sung in the Portland Symphonic Choir, and has performed opera roles with Mocks Crest Productions.</p><div class="clr">&nbsp;</div><h4><img src="http://www.pcctoday.com/monkimage.php?mediaDirectory=mediafiles&amp;mediaId=1682671&amp;fileName=graphic--school-of-music--shaya-lindseth-0-0-107-140.jpg" width="107" height="140" alt="GRAPHIC : School of Music : Shaya Lindseth" title="GRAPHIC : School of Music : Shaya Lindseth" style="float: left; padding-right: 25px; padding-bottom: 25px;">Shaya Lindseth [ piano, voice ]</h4><p>Shaya has more than two decades of music experience &ndash; has taught piano and voice intermittently over the last 12 years for all ages, for varying skill levels. She has a Bachelor of Arts degree in Music from Northwest University, where she played for three choirs: &ldquo;His Praise&rdquo;, &ldquo;One Voice&rdquo;, and &ldquo;Choralons &ldquo; and traveled with PR music teams. She has also been a music director/worship leader for several churches.</p><div class="clr">&nbsp;</div><h4><img src="http://www.pcctoday.com/monkimage.php?mediaDirectory=mediafiles&amp;mediaId=1682665&amp;fileName=graphic--school-of-music--john-anderson-0-0-107-100.jpg" width="107" height="100" alt="GRAPHIC : School of Music : John Anderson" title="GRAPHIC : School of Music : John Anderson" style="float: left; padding-right: 25px; padding-bottom: 25px;"></h4><h4>John Anderson [ guitar, electric bass ]</h4><p>John has been playing for over 25 years and is accomplished in a variety of guitar styles including acoustic, rhythm, lead, worship, rock, and country.&nbsp; He has performed with the bands Coyote Creek and JPX at the Portland Bite, the Pendleton Round Up and on the Good Day Oregon morning show. John teaches guitar, writes songs, and plays in the Portland Christian Center worship bands.</p><div class="clr">&nbsp;</div><h4><img src="http://www.pcctoday.com/monkimage.php?mediaDirectory=mediafiles&amp;mediaId=1729839&amp;fileName=graphic--school-of-music--faculty-katie-leach-0-0-107-150.jpg" width="107" height="150" alt="GRAPHIC : School of Music : Faculty - Katie Leach" title="GRAPHIC : School of Music : Faculty - Katie Leach" style="float: left; padding-right: 25px; padding-bottom: 25px;"></h4><h4>Katie Leach [ dance ]</h4><p>Katie Leach has been a professional dance instructor and choreographer for over 18 years. Specializing in musical theatre styles, she teaches jazz, tap, and ballet to students of all ages. Before her recent co-founding of ENCORE Performing Arts Center in Beaverton, she was a well-known instructor for THPRD. Katie left her hometown of Southern California in 2003 after receiving a B.A. in Dance and Theatre Arts from California State University Fullerton. She is currently pursuing a M.A. in Cross-Cultural Education and Physical Education at National University. Katie also studied Music Education and Vocal Performance at Azusa Pacific. Katie&rsquo;s most noted performances include Snow White with Disneyland Resort Entertainment, Laurie in Oklahoma! and Hot Box Girl in Guys and Dolls. Katie is blessed and grateful for her all-time favorite current roles as a wife and mother.</p><div class="clr">&nbsp;</div><h4>Andrea Irvin-Jones [ violin ]</h4><p>Andrea has earned registration with the American Suzuki Association to teach Suzuki violin books 1-10. She currently performs regularly as a soloist for church services and events and is a teacher for the Portland Suzuki Project. Andrea has a Bechelor of Science degree from Northern Arizona University, where she played in the NAU Orchestra and Flagstaff Symphony.&nbsp;</p>